Package ch.nolix.system.netNeuron

Class NetFrontNeuron<O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.nolix.system.neuronoid.Neuronoid<NetFrontNeuron<O>,java.lang.Object,O>
      • ch.nolix.system.netNeuron.NetFrontNeuron<O>
  • Type Parameters:
    O - The type of the output of a net front neuron.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public final class NetFrontNeuron<O>
extends Neuronoid<NetFrontNeuron<O>,java.lang.Object,O>
implements Closable
    A net front neuron is a neuron that connects to a net back neuron on an other process or machine. A net front neuron is closable.
    Author:
    Silvan Wyss
